replyContent: Thank you so much for playing, support and rating :) There will be updates, but as I am a single person developer things take time. replyContent: Of course you can get a refund. Google has a 2 day refund policy, so you can simply request it and it will be refunded to you. If it is more than 48 hours since your purchase, contact me on support email and I will try to do a manual refund.

content: It's a good game, but the further you go, the more luck-based it gets. I don't like having 2 huge asteroids in my optimal path while getting bombarded by other asteroids outside of it. I'm forced to take the damage sonetimes, with no way of maneuvering around it. So yeah, if it wasn't based so much on luck of the draw, perfect game.
replyContent: Thank you for playing and for your feedback :) It's actually not the luck of the draw. Depending on the mission difficulty, sometimes meteors are intentionally placed on the path, so that you have to go around them, so optimal path is not always going to be available and it is there to test and improve pilot's skills and quick decision making.

content: It's a beautiful game and you did a great effort really and I appreciate all of you.. the gameplay the graphics and the physics are great the planets and the solar system.. but I'm really disappointed because you didn't focus on other things like for example a hover missions , someone to really care about maybe a friend with you ( I mean in story ) .. its repetitive Yes its beautiful but still repetitive gameplay, did you play Whiteout series? .. we need that bond you know what I mean
replyContent:
Thank you for playing and for your feedback :) It's just me that made this game in its entirety, so I had to keep the focus and scope of the product realistic. The main point was to honor the original Lunar Lander game and keep it as an arcade game :) 

That being said, more complex and deep games belonging to the same universe are planned.

content: what's with the endless load screen, haven't actually played yet but am looking forward to it if it will ever load
replyContent: If you are having the issue of not even getting to the Main Menu, check if you have the game installed on external storage. If that is the case, this should be now resolved with the latest update that enables support for external storage (with users permission, of course).

content: Really really fun, challenging and it has great graphics. The most fun I've had on mobile for a long time... but my only complaint is that the asteroid's hitboxes are way off. You are often sure it missed you but you get the damage etc anyway, which is kind of annoying if, like me, you are a perfectionist. Really it's understandable, it's a minor thing, and a masterpiece takes time to craft, and this certainly is a masterpiece of a game, and I hope it grows to be what it deserves :)
replyContent:
Thank you so much for playing and for such wonderful feedback! This means more than I can say :) I hear you regarding the collisions for the meteors. It was perfect before, but that was very taxing on mobile CPUs, so during the optimization process, it had to be a compromise. However, I am working on a solution to that as well :) 

Thank you!
